* Desmonus could feel the vibrations of Zarduss' steps even before he 
entered the room, her bat senses picking up the warm flow of meck-fluid 
running through his veins.
Her stomach couldn't help but rumble at the deliciouse smell of it as he 
came closer.
The vibrations of Zarsus's steps ceased as he walked over to the shattered 
console, the fembot's optics following him as he came into view.
The bonds about her body released and Desmonus couldn't help but sigh, 
sitting up and rubbing her wrists where the bonds had held her.
She quickly slid off of the table, her joints seeming a bit stiff but her 
senses relaxing now that there was no light to bother them.
However, she could't help but stretched her wings out on either side of her 
and her arms as well, every curve on her body taking shape but she hardely 
noticed. Her muscles relaxing more now that they were stretched, her wings 
then folding in to drape over her shoulders and the claws at the end 
connecting to form a natural cloak.
Desmonus watched as Zardus left the console and walked over to her, every 
system in her body telling her that this man was her 
commander...NO...MASTER. And should be treated as such.
Her head blowed as Zardus came up to her but her stomach couldn't help but 
growl in hunger again as the scent of his warm fluid, her senses almost 
seeming to become swamped with the smell.
She indeed WAS hungry.
But, this bot before he would be the only one safe from her feeding bite, 
her systems warning her of that at the very moment.*

" Thank you, Lord. However, my true objectives were only the lights."

* She lifted her head slightly so that she was now looking into his optics, 
her own anber eyes reflecting many things.
Cunning,loyalty, hunger, evil, perfect.*
